<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Differs from all 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Drymonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Drymonia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Drymonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by leaves with a submarginal collecting vein formed by the secondary venation (i.e., brochidodromous), a narrow elongate tubular corolla, and lanceolate calyx lobes with margins laciniate with unbranched filiform serrations. Similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. longiflora" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="longiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. longiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by smaller corolla tube and smaller calyx lobes. Similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. laciniosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="laciniosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. laciniosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by the nearly isophyllous leaves (vs. anisophyllous leaves in 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. laciniosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="laciniosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. laciniosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
